##World's first successful lung transplant for a patient with new coronary pneumonia

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Kuang Xiaoying / Beijing Toutiao client

On March 1, a reporter from the Beijing Youth Daily learned from renowned lung transplant expert Chen Jingyu that on February 29, Chen Jingyu's team successfully performed the world's first double lung transplant operation for new pneumonia in Wuxi. The patient, a 59-year-old man, was diagnosed with NCP. After intubation with ECMO and medication, continuous nucleic acid testing was negative, but both lung functions were severely impaired and irreversible. The patient was stable after surgery.

Industry experts believe that this case of critical cases of new pneumonia lung transplant treatment means to reduce the mortality rate has greater significance.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the early hours of March 1, Chen Jingyu, director of the Lung Transplantation Department of the member of the National People's Congress and deputy director of the Wuxi Municipal People's Hospital of Nanyi University, said that the first transplant of a new pneumonia was completed in Wuxi.

On the morning of March 1, a reporter from the Beijing Youth Daily learned from Chen Jingyu that on February 29, with the full support of the Jiangsu Provincial Health and Health Commission and provincial experts in prevention and control, chen Jingyu's team successfully performed the world's first double-lung transplant in a patient with NCP in Wuxi after a five-hour marathon.

The new case of coronary pneumonia in Jiangsu province, Male, 59 years old, became ill on January 23, was diagnosed COVID-19 on January 26, intubated on February 7, ECMO on February 22, and transferred to Wuxi Infectious Disease Hospital on February 24, continuous nucleic acid tests were negative, but both lung functions were severely impaired and irreversible.

On February 29, with the support of the Health Commission of Jiangsu Province, the Wuxi Health System broke with convention and integrated all medical resources, and a double lung transplant was performed on the case by professor Chen Jingyu's team. Lung source is donated by overseas brain death patients. It was transported to Wuxi by high-speed railway for 7 hours in other provinces. Up to now, the patient has been awake after the operation. The transplanted lungs are well oxygenated and her vital signs are stable.

According to Chen Jingyu, there are three medical preconditions for lung transplantation in patients with new pneumonia: First, the patient is maintained by breathing machine + ECMO, and the failure of both lungs is irreversible; Third, the other organs function is basically normal, the general condition can withstand the lung transplant operation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"This type of surgery is very risky, and the psychological and physical challenges of having transplant doctors and nurses operate in a negative pressure operating room and wearing protective protective clothing throughout the procedure, " Chen said, "In order to successfully transplant patients, and at the same time strive for zero infection of medical staff, with the support of Jiangsu provincial and municipal leaders, the medical team has carried out thorough preparation before the operation. In the next step, the team will closely safeguard the patients, focus on exploring the perioperative management of such patients, do a good job of post-transplant anti-rejection, anti-infection follow-up treatment, and sum up the experience to open the door of hope for more critical cases of late new coronary pneumonia. "
